_json.gridTitle: Vegan Queso Blanco Dip Recipe: Easy, Creamy, and Dreamy!
_json.description: Vegan Queso Blanco Dip "I often use canned coconut milk to introduce a subtly rich dimension... Due to its high-fat content, it adds a supreme richness without imparting any detectable coconut flavor. I discovered that adding just a bit of coconut vinegar to coconut milk creates an authentic mozzarella/stringcheese/ricotta flavor. My latest experiment yielded an amazing vegan queso blanco dip, which tastes exactly like the velvety and rich version you would get in a Mexican restaurant."
